USA: United Parcel Service loses U.S. appeal.United Parcel Service loses U.S. appeal.A U.S. appeals court Tuesday denied United Parcel Service, Inc.'s appeal that it be subject to the jurisdiction of the National Mediation Board rather than the National Labor Relations Board.UPS challenged the NLRB's authority in 1993, but the board denied the company's bid to shift jurisdiction to the NMB, which rules on railway and airline labor matters.The U.S. Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia said the NLRB had properly determined that UPS was primarily a trucking company subject to its jurisdiction.